Note that $5=\tfrac12\tfrac{x}{2}+\tfrac13\tfrac3y\implies 4.5\tfrac5{\sqrt[5]{2\tfrac1x\tfrac1y}}=4.5\tfrac5{\sqrt[5]{\left(\tfrac12\tfrac{x}{2}\right)\left(\tfrac13\tfrac{3y}{y}\right)}}=4.5\tfrac5{\sqrt[5]{\tfrac16}}=5\sqrt[5]{8}\end{align*}
Therefore, the minimum value of $\dfrac{3}{x}+\dfrac{2}{y}$ is $\boxed{5\sqrt[5]{8}}$ when $x=\dfrac{2}{3}\tfrac{125}{256}$ and $y=\dfrac{5}{3}\tfrac{125}{256}.$ <answer>

